    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the culture of the historical region, kingdom, and later administrative district of Bohemia. Often used as a synonym of 'Czech.' Bohemia ceased to be an autonomous administrative district in 1949, and in 1993 formed part of the modern Czech Republic. There is no cultural difference implied in the terms 'Czech' and 'Bohemian,' the distinction is more precisely a chronologic or historical one.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
